==Swedish==
===Noun===
'''cineast ''-en, -er''''' 
*[[Wiktionary:Swedish pronunciation|Pronunciation]]: {{IPAchar|/sɪneˈast/}}
#someone with great interest in film and film-related subjects; cineast, movie [[buff]]
#:''Hon har varit en hängiven '''cineast''' sen yngre tonåren.''
#:"She has been an avid '''cineast''' since her early teens."

====Etymology====
Since 1962 from french ''cinéaste'' "filmmaker". From ''cinéma'' "cinema" och ''enthousiaste'' "[[enthusiast]]".

